By the Central Limit Theorem, \(\bar{X}\) is approximately normally distributed with mean \(0.5\) and standard deviation \(\frac{1}{12}\). The probability \(P\left(\frac{1}{2} \leq \bar{X} \leq \frac{2}{3}\right)\) is standardized using \(Z = \frac{\bar{X} - 0.5}{1/12}\).

