- RR: eyes red (not white)
- RW: eyes white (one red, one white allele)
- WR: eyes white (one white, one red allele, phenotypically same as RW)
- WW: eyes white (two white alleles)

The offspring has white eyes if it has genotype RW, WR, or WW. The probability of white eyes is P(white eyes) = P(RW) + P(WR) + P(WW) = 1/4 + 1/4 + 1/4 = 3/4.

The event of having two white alleles is WW, with P(WW) = 1/4.

The conditional probability of having two white alleles given white eyes is P(WW | white eyes) = P(WW) / P(white eyes) = (1/4) / (3/4) = 1/3 ≈ 0.333.

