- 8% visit neither, so the probability of neither is 0.08.
- The probability of visiting a physical therapist exceeds the probability of visiting a chiropractor by 16 percentage points, meaning the difference is 0.16.

Let \(P\) be the probability of visiting a physical therapist and \(C\) be the probability of visiting a chiropractor.

The probability of visiting either or both is \(1 - 0.08 = 0.92\).

Using the inclusion principle:  
\[P \text{ or } C = P + C - P(\text{both})\]  
\[0.92 = P + C - 0.28\]  
\[P + C = 0.92 + 0.28 = 1.20\]

