- The percentage with normal blood pressure is 100% - 16% - 19% = 65%.
- Of those with normal blood pressure, 11% have irregular heartbeat, so the percentage with irregular heartbeat and normal blood pressure is 0.11 × 65% = 7.15%.
- The percentage with irregular heartbeat and low blood pressure is 17% - 5.95% - 7.15% = 3.90%.
- The percentage with regular heartbeat and low blood pressure is the total with low blood pressure minus those with irregular heartbeat and low blood pressure: 19% - 3.90% = 15.10%.
- Rounded to one decimal place, this is 15.1%.

The final answer is 15.1, as specified in the solution summary.

