- Typical bond length = 1.53 Å
- Force constant \(k_s = 500  \mathrm{N/m}\)
- Change in length \(\Delta x_s = |1.397 - 1.53| = 0.133  \mathrm{\AA} = 1.33 \times 10^{-11}  \mathrm{m}\)
- Energy per single bond \(E_s = \frac{1}{2} \times 500 \times (1.33 \times 10^{-11})^2 = 4.42225 \times 10^{-20}  \mathrm{J}\)
- Total for three single bonds: \(3 \times 4.42225 \times 10^{-20} = 1.326675 \times 10^{-19}  \mathrm{J}\)

For the double bonds:
- Typical bond length = 1.335 Å
- Force constant \(k_d = 950  \mathrm{N/m}\)
